{"word":"αἰκάλλω","slug":"αἰκάλλω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἰκάλλω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>αἰκάλος</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to flatter, wheedle, fondle</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, of a dog, <i>to wag the tail fawningly</i>, <b><a href='S:Babrius'>Babr.</a></b>: (this is prob. the <a href='S:originally'>orig.</a> sense).<p/></div>"}]}